line 698 _zkclient.subscribeStateChanges(this);
at this implementation should always happen later than first synconnected for the reason that ZkClient constructor would call waitTillConnected to guarantee the first synconnect is delivered before proceeding.
Thus first handleNewSession is not delivered from first Synconnect.
By the time handlNewSession is called synchronously from here, it does not necessarily have a valid sessionID. Here, we use waitForEstablishedSession to get a valid sessionID at the time. Otherwise, you have chance to get sessionID 0.
